
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Work Ethic";
}

<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 no-padding">
    <div>
        <img src="~/Content/Images/WorkEthic/Header.png">
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-12 no-padding">
        <div class="col-md-2 no-padding">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/WorkEthic/Construction1.png">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/WorkEthic/Construction2.png">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/WorkEthic/Construction3.png">
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-10">
            <span>The future of A.J. Celiano rests in a daily commitment to principles of service at the highest levels. These principles make up an operational outline for both owners & employees.</span>


            <div>
                <div class="col-md-10">
                    •0n-Time Performance
                    We must always focus on the client's need to receive his project on time. Therefore, on-time performance is required on all projects and nothing less will be accepted.
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-2">
                    <img src="~/Content/Images/WorkEthic/Dan.png">
                </div>
            </div>
            <div>
                •Leadership
                To practice your profession at the highest level of integrity is paramount to providing quality work at a fair price. We reward employees who consistently seek out difficult problems and develop innovative solutions for our clients. Believe that you can make a difference and you will.
            </div>
            <div>
                •Growth
                We encourage employees to use their talents and abilities to improve and grow on a daily basis. Building on the strengths of our staff ensures the ongoing operation and success of the firm.
            </div>
            <div>
                •Quality
                Our ability to maintain client relationships rests on the quality of the services we produce. We will always provide quality without compromise that meets or exceeds our clients' expectations.
            </div>
            <div>
                •Fees
                First class, quality work that is on-time and within budget means profits and continued operation of the firm. We will not be a low-cost provider at the expense of any other goals. Fair rates for fair services.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
